<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000016> rdf:type owl:Class .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023> rdf:type owl:Class .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> rdf:type owl:Class .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_60027
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_60027> rdf:type owl:Class .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000665
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000665> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A role that is realized in some process wherein the bearer is discarded or not utilized further." ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "This definition is preliminary." ;
                                               rdfs:label "waste role"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A mass of solid material which is primarily composed of plastic."@en ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000412> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo.owl> ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2996-719X> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8166-0486> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1072-8081> ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> "Plastikstück"@de ,
                                                                                                              "pedazo de plástico"@es ,
                                                                                                              "pezzo di plastica"@it ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> "envoPlastics"@es ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology:
We imported this hierarchy of EnvO classes with the purpose of including an alternative system of classification of plastic debris particles and mapping it with that proposed by Hartmann et al. (2019), covered within the ClimOO Ontology. The alignment applies only with regard to particle size as a matter of example.

EnvO classes for plastic debris particles do not present axioms besides the subsumption relation to the “piece of plastic” class. Class meaning concerning particle size only resides within the definitions.

We import the “piece of plastic” class without including the related axiomatization and subsume this class directly to BFO: object class, as we imported it solely for grouping purposes. It is not relevant for the alignment.

We envision discussions with EnvO's curators to consolidate this alignment, especially in terms of class axiomatization."""@en ;
                                               rdfs:label "piece of plastic"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000777
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000777> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105010> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A plastic pellet which is produced such that its size allows it to be rapidly melted and used as input for further downstream manufacturing processes."@en ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000412> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo.owl> ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2996-719X> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4366-3088> ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> "envoPlastics" ;
                                               rdfs:label "nurdle"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A piece of plastic which has a diameter less than five millimetres." ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000412> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo.owl> ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2996-719X> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8166-0486> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1072-8081> ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym> "microplastic" ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> "envoPlastics" ;
                                               rdfs:comment "This classification is based on the thresholds detailed in GESAMP report # 99 on recommendation from the SDG 14 indicator team. While the definition is in accordance with the common use of this term (as per GESAMP report # 99), alternative size classifications exist. Alternative classifications are a piece of plastic which is between 1 and 5 millimetres in diameter, a piece of plastic which has a diameter less than 1 millimetre, or a piece of plastic which has a diameter greater than 330 micrometres. The use of the word diameter in this case was understood to mean the generalised form of diameter, i.e. the largest distance between two points belonging to an object."@en ;
                                               rdfs:label "microplastic particle"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000945
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000945> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A microplastic particle which is the direct output of a manufacturing process." ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000412> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo.owl> ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2996-719X> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8166-0486> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1072-8081> ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> "Primäres Mikroplastik"@de ,
                                                                                                              "microplastica primaria"@it ,
                                                                                                              "microplástico primario"@es ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym> "microplastic" ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> "envoPlastics" ;
                                               rdfs:label "primary microplastic particle"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000946
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000946> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A microplastic particle which is derived from the breakdown of larger plastic debris." ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000412> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo.owl> ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2996-719X> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8166-0486> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1072-8081> ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> "Sekundäres Mikroplastik"@de ,
                                                                                                              "microplastica secondaria"@it ,
                                                                                                              "microplástico secundario"@es ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym> "microplastic" ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> "envoPlastics" ;
                                               rdfs:comment "The debris that make up the Great Pacific Garbage Patch constantly release microplastics as they break down." ;
                                               rdfs:label "secondary microplastic particle"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105002
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105002> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000016> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A disposition inhering in a bearer by virtue of that bearer's ability to, repeatedly, become plastic on heating and harden again on cooling."@en ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2996-719X> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1072-8081> ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/creator> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8166-0486> ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date> "2021-04-27T09:10:14Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> "termoplasticità"@it ,
                                                                                                              "熱塑性"@zh ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> "envoPlastics"@en ;
                                               rdfs:label "thermoplasticity"@en .

